setup the global editor 
by default git uses nano as editor we can set to the vim 
git config --global core.editor "vim"

Head  is pointer which points to the latest commit 

Git reset  
this command works  with only in  local repository 
if you want to undo a commit 

 
git reset --soft 
git reset --soft  HEAD~1
commit id is deleted  
Move the file to the staging area 

git mixed  => mixed
git reset --mixed HEAD~2
it will always delete the commit   
files  will back to  the working area which is untracke

Git Hard 
git reset  --hard HEAD~2
commit is also deleted 
files and content associated with file is also deleted.
we can't recover the file 

